  <section class="container">
    <h1>What is Buddhism?</h1>
    <p class="lead">Buddhism was founded by Shakyamuni Buddha around 3,000 years ago in India. He witnessed the suffering of people from every walk of life and searched for a way to end that suffering.</p>
    <p>Buddhism teaches a path that leads to true freedom from pain, delusion, and dissatisfaction. It points to the potential within every person to awaken wisdom and compassion right where they are.</p>
    <h2>Key ideas</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The understanding of suffering and its causes.</li>
      <li>The possibility of transforming one’s life through awakening.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>This path ultimately leads to the Mystic Law of Nam-Myoho-Renge-Kyo, which Nichiren Daishonin revealed so that all people can achieve Buddhahood in the Latter Day of the Law.</p>

